ID <- as_factor(FFA_excel$ID[1:40])

Preparing dataframes for analysis

CE

CE <- as.data.frame(subset(CE_excel, select = -c(ID, group, gender_group)))
CE <- CE[, which(colMeans(!is.na(CE)) > 0.7)]
FFA <- as_tibble(CE)
# Replace with minimum value in range of DF
selected_columns <- c(1:(ncol(CE)))
CE[selected_columns] <- lapply(CE[selected_columns], 
                                  function(x) 
                                    replace(x,is.na(x), min(x, na.rm = T)
                                            ))
# scaling data
CE <- as.matrix(CE)
CE <- scale(CE)
CE_BL <- CE[1:40,]
CE_AI <- CE[41:80,]

CER

CER <- as.data.frame(subset(CER_excel, select = -c(ID, group, gender_group)))
CER <- CER[, which(colMeans(!is.na(CER)) > 0.7)]
CER <- as_tibble(CER)
# Replace with minimum value in range of DF
selected_columns <- c(1:(ncol(CER)))
CER[selected_columns] <- lapply(CER[selected_columns], 
                                  function(x) 
                                    replace(x,is.na(x), min(x, na.rm = T)
                                            ))
# Median Normalization
CER <- as.matrix(CER)
CER <- medianNormalization(CER, noLogTransform = TRUE)
CER_BL <- CER[1:40,]
CER_AI <- CER[41:80,]

Heatmaps

CE

# Melting dataframe for heatmap
CE_BL_melt <- melt(CE_BL)
## Warning in type.convert.default(X[[i]], ...): 'as.is' should be specified by
## the caller; using TRUE
CE_BL_melt$X1 <- ID
CE_AI_melt <- melt(CE_AI)
## Warning in type.convert.default(X[[i]], ...): 'as.is' should be specified by
## the caller; using TRUE
CE_AI_melt$X1 <- ID
# Initializing heatmap via ggplot2
CE_BL_ggp <- ggplot(CE_BL_melt, aes(X1,X2)) +
  geom_tile(aes(fill = value)) + scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "orange") +
  ggtitle('BL') + theme(legend.position = "none", axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45),
          axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45)) + labs(y = "Species", x = "ID")

CE_AI_ggp <- ggplot(CE_AI_melt, aes(X1,X2)) +
  geom_tile(aes(fill = value)) + scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "orange") +
  ggtitle('AI')+ theme(axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45),
          axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45)) + labs(y = "Species", x = "ID")
# Patchwork BL and AI graphs together
CE_BL_ggp + CE_AI_ggp

  geom_tile(aes(fill = value)) + scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "orange") +
  ggtitle('BL') + theme(legend.position = "none", axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45),
          axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45)) + labs(y = "Species", x = "ID")

LPC_AI_ggp <- ggplot(LPC_AI_melt, aes(X1, X2)) +
  geom_tile(aes(fill = value)) + scale_fill_gradient(low = "black", high = "orange") +
  ggtitle('AI')+ theme(axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45),
          axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", 
                           size=6, angle=45)) + labs(y = "Species", x = "ID")
# Patchwork BL and AI graphs together
LPC_BL_ggp + LPC_AI_ggp
